title: Add F-Droid build flavor (Closes #128) (#162)
message:
Add F-Droid build flavor (Closes #128) (#162)

* Move getSafeNameForSensor to StardroidApplication

It's only used there and allows use to make Analytics an interface
later.

* Cleanup build script

- Add -e to error on build failures.
- Use subshell instead of cd ..
- Manually fix classpath because gradle has problems with flavors

* Extract Analytics.java content into an interface

* Add AbstractGooglePlayServicesChecker.java

This adds an abstract class for the gms independent parts of
GooglePlayServicesChecker.java.

* Add support-v4 compile dependency

This is used in GooglePlayServicesChecker.java

* Add AbstractDynamicStarMapModule.java

This adds a base class for the gms independent parts of
DynamicStarMapModule.java.

* Separate build flavors for gms and fdroid

This adds two build flavors. One using gms (analytics and location) and
one without for F-Droid. All classes using gms are moved to the flavor
source path and a version without gms is added or the fdroid flavor.

Change the way we deal with devices lacking a sensor.

title: Change the way we deal with devices lacking a sensor.  Instead of blocking the…
message: Change the way we deal with devices lacking a sensor.  Instead of blocking the use of automode, we just warn the user that it might not work.  This is because some devices like the Moto E are falsely marketed as lacking a compass (and the SensorManager reports its absence)...but they actually do have one and Sky Map works on them just fine.  Yay marketing.

title: Intermediate reworking of the constellation writer, which is failing to output a…
message:
Intermediate reworking of the constellation writer, which is failing to output a bunch of constellation names.
Root cause is that it tries to match each constellation to its 'closest' label.  So some constellations will get the label
twice, and some not at all.  At the moment we don't have the ability to select individual constellations so it
doesn't really matter which one they get added to.
